CAPE TOWN, South Africa, January 18, 2023/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The Commission for Gender Equality (CGE) is pleased to announce the appointment of its new Chief Executive Officer (CEO), Ms Phelisa Nkomo, who has started her duties as of January 2023. The CGE regards this appointment as a milestone and boost in performing its constitutional mandate of working towards a society free of gender inequality.
                                As part of her initial engagements, Ms Nkomo will on Friday, 20 January 2023, meet with selected stakeholders who will be representing Chapter 9 institutions in South Africa
                            



As part of her initial engagements, Ms Nkomo will on Friday, 20 January 2023, meet with selected stakeholders who will be representing Chapter 9 institutions, the South African Police Service, the Gauteng Provincial Government and non-governmental organisations who are involved in the fight against gender-based violence and gender inequality in South Africa.